1114
01:03:48.942 --> 01:03:51.602
neutrophil state. And we started to look using 16S,

1115
01:03:52.482 --> 01:03:54.822
is there dysbiosis in the cachectic tumors?

1116
01:03:55.722 --> 01:03:59.642
And you can see here an example of a cachectic versus non-cachectic tumor,

1117
01:04:00.562 --> 01:04:04.202
where the density of the 16S in the tumors is much greater in the

1118
01:04:04.222 --> 01:04:05.042
cachectic animals.

1119
01:04:06.031 --> 01:04:09.942
I should also note that these are much stronger

1120
01:04:10.262 --> 01:04:13.682
when the tumor is located near the airway, suggesting that

1121
01:04:14.202 --> 01:04:18.091
the increase in the tumor next to the airway can promote this

1122
01:04:18.122 --> 01:04:19.182
dysbiotic phenotype.

1123
01:04:21.802 --> 01:04:25.042
And data from a collaborator at NYU, Leo

1124
01:04:25.102 --> 01:04:28.732
Segal, had a very nice experiment that's

1125
01:04:28.962 --> 01:04:32.922
helping us validate some of these findings, where he uses a tumor cell line

1126
01:04:32.962 --> 01:04:36.642
that does not induce cachexia. You can see here in green,

1127
01:04:37.122 --> 01:04:41.082
this wild-type cell line, which is KRAS driven, loss of

1128
01:04:41.122 --> 01:04:41.692
TP53.

1129
01:04:42.642 --> 01:04:45.482
You don't get any weight loss. You also have very low neutrophils.

1130
01:04:46.712 --> 01:04:49.342
And you can also give mice a dysbiotic cocktail,

1131
01:04:50.342 --> 01:04:54.302
which includes bacteria that can modulate directly

1132
01:04:54.322 --> 01:04:57.942
into the lungs, and they house in the lungs, and they produce a small

1133
01:04:57.982 --> 01:05:01.882
inflammatory reaction. If you do that alone without the tumor cells, you also

1134
01:05:01.902 --> 01:05:05.021
don't lose weight, but you generate a little bit of neutrophilia.

1135
01:05:07.182 --> 01:05:10.242
I'm sorry, the green line is the wild-type mice, no tumors.

1136
01:05:10.662 --> 01:05:11.102
The

1137
01:05:12.042 --> 01:05:14.082
gray line here is the tumor-bearing mice,

1138
01:05:14.922 --> 01:05:17.742
which don't have much weight loss and don't have many neutrophils.

1139
01:05:18.102 --> 01:05:21.922
And then you combine the two, where you have tumor cells that are implanted

1140
01:05:22.002 --> 01:05:25.102
and the dysbiosis, and now you have much worse survival.

1141
01:05:25.442 --> 01:05:29.242
You have induction of weight loss dramatically, and you

1142
01:05:29.282 --> 01:05:31.042
have much more neutrophils present.

1143
01:05:34.062 --> 01:05:37.002
So just to summarize our current thinking on this model,

1144
01:05:38.202 --> 01:05:41.962
I think that there is likely a dysbiosis occurring because of the

1145
01:05:41.982 --> 01:05:45.362
tumor, possibly due to the tumor location near large airways.

1146
01:05:46.462 --> 01:05:50.042
This is activating local myeloid cells that are producing

1147
01:05:50.182 --> 01:05:53.082
prostaglandin E2. These prostaglandins can

1148
01:05:53.922 --> 01:05:54.782
reduce food intake.

1149
01:05:55.762 --> 01:05:59.701
And the presence of these neutrophils and myeloid suppressor cells are also

1150
01:05:59.722 --> 01:06:02.201
blocking the efficacy of the checkpoint inhibitors.

1151
01:06:04.082 --> 01:06:07.422
And ongoing work is now manipulating each of these components.

1152
01:06:08.442 --> 01:06:12.402
First, we're trying to manipulate neutrophils, several ongoing and complementary

1153
01:06:12.502 --> 01:06:14.982
strategies. This is actually very challenging.

1154
01:06:15.142 --> 01:06:18.382
Many of you, if you've worked with trying to manipulate neutrophils, they're very

1155
01:06:18.462 --> 01:06:22.402
short-lived, and removing them often is transient, and they

1156
01:06:22.442 --> 01:06:26.142
come back with a vengeance. And so we have some strategies here,

1157
01:06:26.182 --> 01:06:28.322
including a DPP1 inhibitor that we're testing.

1158
01:06:29.722 --> 01:06:33.562
And also, we've shown through genetic manipulation that

1159
01:06:33.742 --> 01:06:37.282
lowering prostaglandin production can improve cachexia

1160
01:06:37.302 --> 01:06:40.962
outcomes, and we're now interested in possibly blocking this signal

1161
01:06:41.442 --> 01:06:45.262
using inhibitors that are available for, that were designed to

1162
01:06:45.322 --> 01:06:48.962
mitigate pain responses that target the sensory neurons and can block the

1163
01:06:49.002 --> 01:06:51.212
effects of prostaglandins on those sensory

1164
01:06:51.242 --> 01:06:55.138
neurons.And again, I'll just

1165
01:06:55.178 --> 01:06:55.678
highlight

1166
01:06:56.498 --> 01:07:00.198
what we talked about today, which is components of the tumor microenvironment,

1167
01:07:00.658 --> 01:07:04.338
including immune cells, can produce soluble

1168
01:07:04.358 --> 01:07:08.298
factors that can manipulate both cachexia and checkpoint inhibitor

1169
01:07:08.318 --> 01:07:08.818
response.

